# Learning about {{site.data.keyword.logs_routing_full_notm}}
{: #about}

You can use {{site.data.keyword.logs_routing_full_notm}} to collect and route {{site.data.keyword.cloud_notm}} logs from your account to a configured target. You can also route logs from applications on your [{{site.data.keyword.containerlong_notm}}](/docs/containers) or [{{site.data.keyword.openshiftlong_notm}}](/docs/openshift) clusters.
{: shortdesc}

## Log sources
{: #about_sources}

Logs can be received by {{site.data.keyword.logs_routing_full}} from two sources:

* Log data sent to {{site.data.keyword.logs_routing_full}} by {{site.data.keyword.cloud_notm}} [services that support {{site.data.keyword.logs_routing_full}}.](/docs/logs-router?topic=logs-router-cloud_services_locations)

* Applications with a running {{site.data.keyword.logs_routing_full}} agent on [{{site.data.keyword.containerlong_notm}}](/docs/containers) or [{{site.data.keyword.openshiftlong_notm}}](/docs/openshift) clusters.

![Flow of logs routed with the {{site.data.keyword.logs_routing_full}} agent](../images/Logs-Router-05.svg "Flow of logs routed with the {{site.data.keyword.logs_routing_full}} agent"){: caption="Figure 1. Flow of logs routed with the {{site.data.keyword.logs_routing_full}} agent" caption-side="bottom"}

## Tenants and targets
{: #about_tenant_target}

{{site.data.keyword.logs_routing_full_notm}} uses tenants and targets.

{{site.data.content.tenant_definition-paragraph}}

An {{site.data.keyword.cloud_notm}} account can have 1 configured {{site.data.keyword.logs_routing_full_notm}} tenant. This tenant can have 1 configured target.

{{site.data.keyword.logs_routing_full_notm}} supports only {{site.data.keyword.la_full_notm}} instances as targets. These instances can be in the same account, a different account, and the same or different region as the {{site.data.keyword.logs_routing_full_notm}} tenant.
{: important}

## Determining the origin of {{site.data.keyword.cloud_notm}} log data
{: #about_data_origin}

You can determine the {{site.data.keyword.cloud_notm}} service routing log data by the `logSourceCRN` value that is included in the log line. The `logSourceCRN` value is the [Cloud Resource Name (CRN)](docs/account?topic=account-crn) of the originating {{site.data.keyword.cloud_notm}} service.

This value is not provided for logs that are sent by the {{site.data.keyword.logs_routing_full_notm}} agent.
{: note}


